<span class="section-label">// Process</span><h2 class="section-title">How It Works</h2>
<p class="section-desc">Whether we find you or you call us &mdash; we move fast. From first contact to active response within hours.</p>
<div class="timeline">
<div class="timeline-step"><span class="step-number">01 // ALERT</span><h3 class="step-title">Detection or Contact</h3><p class="step-desc">We detect your exposure via dark web monitoring &mdash; or you call us directly. Either way, the clock starts now and we respond immediately.</p></div>
<div class="timeline-step"><span class="step-number">02 // TRIAGE</span><h3 class="step-title">Rapid Triage</h3><p class="step-desc">A senior practitioner scopes the incident within the first hour. Attack type, affected systems, and immediate priorities are established before anything else.</p></div>
<div class="timeline-step"><span class="step-number">03 // CONTAIN</span><h3 class="step-title">Contain &amp; Investigate</h3><p class="step-desc">We stop the bleeding while preserving evidence. Forensic investigation, attacker timeline, and negotiation advisory run in parallel &mdash; not sequentially.</p></div>
<div class="timeline-step"><span class="step-number">04 // RECOVER</span><h3 class="step-title">Recover &amp; Harden</h3><p class="step-desc">Clean recovery, regulatory notifications, and a post-incident report your board and insurer can rely on. Root cause remediated, not patched over.</p></div>
</div></div></section>

